## Why no per-phase Discuss?

The Schema Recovery Procedure is deterministic once the project-level defaults in `CONTEXT.md` are locked. Each phase's constraint-handling decisions follow mechanically from those defaults (e.g., NOT NULL → mandatory, PK → preferred UC). There is nothing per-phase to debate — every phase runs `plan → execute → verify → ship`.

The text-flow (`bootstrap.sh --text`) keeps the full five verbs because CSDP is dialogue-driven; that asymmetry is documented in the integration's README.

